    </string>
    <string id="25">
        <![CDATA[This cramped, shadowy passage is thick with the stenches of smoke, sour sweat, and despair. You hear a single, constant, low moan, coming from farther down the corridor.]]>
    </string>
    <string id="26">
        <![CDATA[When he takes his death blow, Jaen has no final words, no dying speech to rally his followers. His final sound is a scream of fury. He howls out his anger at you, and his frustration with his failure.]]>
    </string>
    <string id="27">
        <![CDATA[Then his scream fades to a gurgle, and ends. With the crash of armor on cobblestones, he keels over. The rebels have achieved another great victory.]]>
    </string>
    <string id="28">
        <![CDATA[Jaen's men are stunned by his loss, but not for long. Professionals to the last, they soon return to the attack, but not before you're able to pick up and pocket the key that bounced out of Jaen's pocket.]]>
    </string>
    <string id="32">
        <![CDATA[You stand at the entrance to a huge meeting hall, dominated by a huge oak table and many massive, granite pillars. The place is a strange echo of Stalker's meeting chamber, eerily similar in many ways.]]>
    </string>
    <string id="33">
        <![CDATA[At last, you have come face to face with the leader of the Empire troops on Morrow's Isle. As imposing as the architecture is, however, it is nothing compared to the infamous Jaen himself.]]>
    </string>
    <string id="34">
        <![CDATA[This is no spy, or diplomat. This man has clearly spent much of his life as a soldier. He stands well over six feet tall, and his massive frame is clad in equally imposing plate armor. The enormous hammer at his side could fell an ox in a single blow.]]>
    </string>
    <string id="35">
        <![CDATA[You seem to have intruded on one of his strategy sessions, and all his lieutenants are present. A nastier bunch of heavily armed men, you'd have a hard time imagining. But here they all are, and they're all about to try and kill you.]]>
    </string>
    <string id="38">
        <![CDATA[You find a small hole in the ground. Not so small you couldn't slide down it, but small enough that it would be a painful process. You may not be able to make it back up, either.]]>
    </string>
    <string id="39">
        <![CDATA[Still, if this is the only safe way into Jaen's fortress, you may have no choice ...]]>
    </string>
    <string id="44">
        <![CDATA[You shimmy down the hole. Again. And fall into a massive pile of filth. Again.]]>
    </string>
    <string id="45">
        <![CDATA[You start to shimmy down the hole. At first, you climb down carefully and in a controlled way. Unfortunately, the hole becomes rather slick. Before long, you lose your grip, and start sliding down.]]>
    </string>
    <string id="46">
        <![CDATA[You don't have long to fall. Soon, you're dumped out of a crack in the ceiling of a small cave, and fall into a huge pile of rotting garbage. It breaks your fall, but not in a pleasant way. You're now in Jaen's Fortress.]]>
    </string>
    <string id="47">
        <![CDATA[After you broke into Jaen's Fortress for the first time, Jaen spared no effort to find the hole in his defenses. He found it, and, expecting someone would try to use it again, placed 100 strong men here to ambush whoever came through.]]>
    </string>
    <string id="48">
        <![CDATA[After you are overwhelmed and captured and before you are executed, Jaen's interrogators get you to tell them everything they need to know about Jaen's forces and defenses.]]>
    </string>
    <string id="49">
        <![CDATA[You hear many shouts of alarm and readiness. More guards have arrived from outside the fortress.]]>
    </string>
    <string id="50">
        <![CDATA[As you get close to the gate into the main part of the fortress, you hear the all too familiar report of a Hill Runner explosive box. The blast is of comparable power to the one which destroyed Lord Volpe's fortress.]]>
    </string>
    <string id="51">
        <![CDATA[The explosion was to the east. On the down side, the forces here will be alerted. On the up side, the distraction should be enough to get you in to kill Jaen.]]>
    </string>
    <string id="56">
        <![CDATA[From here, you can see the result of the explosion. They destroyed the front gate of Jaen's fortress. You're thankful for it now. The hole in the wall will make it much easier for you to escape.]]>
    </string>
    <string id="57">
        <![CDATA[You emerge from the well concealed cave entrance. It's covered by a magical illusion. It's amazing the rebels were able to find it. You'll be surprised if you're able to find it again.]]>
    </string>
    <string id="58">
        <![CDATA[Not that you would want to ... you were lucky to survive this attack. The next time they will be more than ready for you. Your mission was completed. Stalker will be very pleased.]]>
    </string>
    <string id="59">
        <![CDATA[You are very relieved to have escaped Jaen's fortress with your hides intact. Unfortunately, Jaen is still alive, and he spares no effort to chase you down before you can get far. Hordes of troops swarm over the countryside.]]>
    </string>
    <string id="60">
        <![CDATA[After you are overwhelmed and captured and before you are executed, Jaen's interrogators get you to tell them everything they need to know about Stalker's forces and defenses.]]>
    </string>
    <string id="61">
        <![CDATA[After a long march north, you reach the river. At first, you think that you have made some sort of mistake - you were supposed to have reached Jaen's fortress by now.]]>
    </string>
    <string id="62">
        <![CDATA[As you wander around, you notice a hole in the ground. It's a recently dug shaft, framed with rough timbers. You walk up to it to investigate. As you peer over the edge, you notice people approaching you from all sides.]]>
    </string>
    <string id="63">
        <![CDATA[They're Hill Runners. Only they could be this stealthy. One of them says "We've been waiting for you. Everything is in place. It is time. Climb down the hole."]]>
    </string>
    <string id="64">
        <![CDATA[When you express your doubts about entering the hole, they don't hesitate to grab you and chuck you in. You land on a thick pile of furs below ...]]>
    </string>
</town>
